<p>
  <% if @details.count == 1 %>
    <%= worldcon_basic_greeting.capitalize %> <%= @details.first %>!
  <% else %>
    <%= worldcon_greeting_sentence_excited %>
  <% end %>
</p>

<%# TODO: Deal with date parts %>

<p>
  Hello eligible Hugo nominator! This is just a quick reminder to let you know
  that the end of the Hugo nomination period is fast approaching! The deadline
  for nominations is <%= hugo_nom_deadline %>.
</p>

<%# TODO: Deal with the number of categories %>
<p>
  As a member of <%= worldcon_public_name %>, you are eligible to nominate in the 17 Hugo ballot
  categories covering the best of the genre in the last year, for the Lodestar
  Award for Best Young Adult Book, the Astounding Award for Best New Writer
  (formerly known as the John W. Campbell Award), and for the <%= retro_hugo_75_ago %> Retro Hugos,
  celebrating the genre work of <%= (retro_hugo_year_75_.to_i - 1).to_s %>.
</p>

<%# TODO: Deal with the URLs %>
<p>
  To nominate online, please visit
  <a href=<%= member_login_url %>>the members' area</a> and
  enter the email address
  you received this email at, and request a login link. After clicking the link
  and entering the members area, click on My Memberships to access all
  memberships linked with that email address. Then click the nominating links on
  your membership.
</p>

<p>
  You can make up to five nominations in each category. Be sure to hit the save
  button once you have made your nominations. You can save each category
  individually, or save them all at once using the button at the bottom of the
  ballot. You can make as many changes as you like to your nomination ballots
  until the deadline. Your current ballot will be emailed to you an hour after
  you stop making changes to it.
</p>

<%# TODO: Deal with dates %>
<p>
  We expect to announce the final ballot in early April, and the awards will be
  presented at <%= worldcon_public_name %>, which will run from July 29 to August 2, 2020.
</p>

<p>
  The Hugo Awards are fan-run, fan-given, and fan-supported. We recommend that
  you nominate whatever works and creators you have personally read or seen that
  were your favorites from <%= (worldcon_year.to_i - 1).to_s %> and <%= (retro_hugo_year.to_i - 1).to_s %>.
</p>

<p>
  Please contact <%= hugo_help_email %> if you have difficulties accessing the
  online ballot(s), or you have any other questions on the Hugo process.
</p>

<%# deal with URLS %>
<p>
  A printable version of the WSFS Constitution and Hugo Nominating ballot has
  been included in the mailed-out version of Progress Report 2. You may also
  download a printable ballot in
  <a href=<%= hugo_ballot_download_a4 %>>A4</a>,
  or
  <a href=<%= hugo_ballot_download_letter %>>US letter</a>
  sizes. The WSFS Constitution is also available online
  <a href=<%= wsfs_constitution_link %>>here</a>.
</p>

<p>
  We look forward to your participation in the <%= worldcon_year %> Hugo Awards and <%= retro_hugo_year %> Retro
  Hugos, and hope to see you at <%= worldcon_public_name %>!
</p>

<%# deal with organizer names%>
<p>
  <%= organizers_names_for_signature %><br>
  Hugo Administrator and Deputy Hugo Administrators
</p>
